<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Thieves are not too viable</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:26 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Thieves are not too viable<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=777" TARGET=_self>Re: Sup Az. Yes I'll have a char there</A> (Azeraab)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>From what my friends with thieves have told me they are a waste in PvP combat, and they had given up on them. You can get some nice damage off with a backstab but it is next to impossible I hear to backstab anyone who is aware of your presence.
<BR>Perhaps others with more PvP experiene with EQ thieves can comment?
<P>I think Mages, especially Druids, and Monks will have the upper hand. Clerics will always have a place in PvP groups as should Shamans. I found my Shaman actually did quite well solo against fighters, but I need to test her more against spellcasters. Any class that cannot gate is just asking for trouble IMO. With the current system the only kills will probably happen to those weakened by monsters and/or caught and trapped by gangs in tight spaces. Being able to gate out of a dungeon is going to be a big plus. A halfling thief might be able to hide, as I don't know how other characters can detect a halfling once they are hidden (unless the halfling fails a hiding check).
<P>&gt; Perhaps I will go with a thief then. I'm wondering if they will
<BR>&gt; be viable in PvP. I'm sure druids will be nerfed.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
